      • into

        MergeTupleWithRepositoryProvider<org.javatuples.Tuple> into(List<Class<? extends AggregateRoot<?>>> aggregateRootClasses)
        Merge the dto into a tuple of aggregate roots. This method is not recommended.

        If you can, use the method matching the number of aggregate roots you have in the tuple. For instance use into(Class, Class) for a Pair&lt;Customer, Order&gt;. The result will be a more typed.

        Parameters:
        aggregateRootClasses - a list of aggregate root classes
        Returns:
        a tuple of aggregate roots

      • into

        @Deprecated
void into(org.javatuples.Tuple aggregateRoots)
        Deprecated. 
        Merge the dto into a tuple of aggregate roots. This method is not recommended.

        If you can, use the method matching the number of aggregate roots you have in the tuple. For instance use into(org.seedstack.business.api.domain.AggregateRoot, org.seedstack.business.api.domain.AggregateRoot) for a Pair&lt;Customer, Order&gt; it will return a more typed result.

        Parameters:
        aggregateRoots - a list of aggregate root classes
